    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This update makes [two tests fail](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/3585b18367d477d43c3db961ae153e7991151671/src/components/RangeInput/__tests__/RangeInput-test.js#L70-L118), even with these changes (not pushed to the branch):\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n- component.instance().componentWillReceiveProps(nextProps);\r\n+ component.setProps(nextProps);\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo you know what could cause that? cc @samouss \r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>Ouput</summary>\r\n\r\n```\r\n  ● RangeInput › willReceiveProps › expect to update the empty state from given props\r\n\r\n    expect(value).toMatchSnapshot()\r\n\r\n    Received value does not match stored snapshot \"RangeInput willReceiveProps expect to update the empty state from given props 2\".\r\n\r\n    - Snapshot\r\n    + Received\r\n\r\n    @@ -1,7 +1,7 @@\r\n      <div\r\n    -   className=\"root noRefinement\"\r\n    +   className=\"root\"\r\n      >\r\n        <form\r\n          className=\"form\"\r\n          onSubmit={[Function]}\r\n        >\r\n    @@ -15,10 +15,11 @@\r\n              min={0}\r\n              onChange={[Function]}\r\n              placeholder={0}\r\n              step={1}\r\n              type=\"number\"\r\n    +         value={20}            />\r\n          </label>\r\n          <Template\r\n            data={Object {}}\r\n            rootProps={\r\n    @@ -42,10 +43,11 @@\r\n              min={0}\r\n              onChange={[Function]}\r\n              placeholder={500}\r\n              step={1}\r\n              type=\"number\"\r\n    +         value={480}\r\n            />\r\n          </label>\r\n          <Template\r\n            data={Object {}}\r\n            rootProps={\r\n\r\n      83 |       component.setProps(nextProps);\r\n      84 |\r\n    > 85 |       expect(component).toMatchSnapshot();\r\n         |                         ^\r\n      86 |       expect(component.state()).toEqual({\r\n      87 |         min: 20,\r\n      88 |         max: 480,\r\n\r\n      at Object.toMatchSnapshot (src/components/RangeInput/__tests__/RangeInput-test.js:85:25)\r\n\r\n  ● RangeInput › willReceiveProps › expect to update the state from given props\r\n\r\n    expect(value).toMatchSnapshot()\r\n\r\n    Received value does not match stored snapshot \"RangeInput willReceiveProps expect to update the state from given props 2\".\r\n\r\n    - Snapshot\r\n    + Received\r\n\r\n    @@ -15,11 +15,11 @@\r\n              min={0}\r\n              onChange={[Function]}\r\n              placeholder={0}\r\n              step={1}\r\n              type=\"number\"\r\n    -         value={40}\r\n    +         value={20}\r\n            />\r\n          </label>\r\n          <Template\r\n            data={Object {}}\r\n            rootProps={\r\n    @@ -43,11 +43,11 @@\r\n              min={0}\r\n              onChange={[Function]}\r\n              placeholder={500}\r\n              step={1}\r\n              type=\"number\"\r\n    -         value={460}\r\n    +         value={480}\r\n            />\r\n          </label>\r\n          <Template\r\n            data={Object {}}\r\n            rootProps={\r\n\r\n      111 |       component.setProps(nextProps);\r\n      112 |\r\n    > 113 |       expect(component).toMatchSnapshot();\r\n          |                         ^\r\n      114 |       expect(component.state()).toEqual({\r\n      115 |         min: 20,\r\n      116 |         max: 480,\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>",
